 Changing this takes effect whenever an application requests memory.
 
 
+anon_min_ratio
+==============
+
+This value provides hard protection for anonymous pages on each node.
+Anonymous pages are not reclaimed when their amount is below this percentage
+of node memory.
+
+This can reduce swap thrashing when compressed swap absorbs memory pressure.
+Setting this value too high can make anonymous memory harder to reclaim and
+can trigger earlier out-of-memory kills.
+
+The unit is a percentage of the node memory. The default value is controlled
+by CONFIG_ANON_MIN_RATIO.
+
+
+clean_low_ratio
+===============
+
+This value provides best-effort protection for clean file pages on each node.
+Clean file pages are avoided under memory pressure while their amount is below
+this percentage of node memory, unless reclaim pressure escalates toward OOM.
+
+This can reduce file-cache churn under mixed desktop and build workloads.
+Setting this value too high can push more pressure toward anonymous pages and
+swap.
+
+The unit is a percentage of the node memory. The default value is controlled
+by CONFIG_CLEAN_LOW_RATIO.
+
+
+clean_min_ratio
+===============
+
+This value provides hard protection for clean file pages on each node. Clean
+file pages are not reclaimed when their amount is below this percentage of node
+memory.
+
+This can preserve a small file-cache floor during memory pressure. Setting
+this value too high can trigger earlier out-of-memory kills when other memory
+types cannot be reclaimed.
+
+The unit is a percentage of the node memory. The default value is controlled
+by CONFIG_CLEAN_MIN_RATIO.
+
+
 compact_memory
 ==============
 
@@ -1111,6 +1160,19 @@
 can then be used to tune kswapd aggressiveness accordingly.
 
 
+workingset_protection
+=====================
+
+This enables or disables the anon_min_ratio, clean_low_ratio, and
+clean_min_ratio reclaim protections.
+
+When this is set to 1, reclaim computes node-local anonymous and clean-file
+page floors from the configured ratios. When this is set to 0, reclaim ignores
+the ratio floors.
+
+The default value is 1.
+
+
 zone_reclaim_mode
